  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare the effect of three different non-pharmacological
      interventions (usually practiced in ambulatory care of Childhood Obesity (AmO), physical
      activity program (IFSP) and diet therapy adjusted estimate by indirect calorimetry) on the
      percentage of body fat and basal metabolism of children and Overweight and obesity in the
      metropolitan region of Porto Alegre (RS).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
